item.description:
@s_3_3_m_3 wrote:

haywad:

i know but everytime a download one it doesnt work or i cant compile it or something

Pretty much every server i download i can’t compile either, you have to edit the compiler, go to your java in your program files, and find your version for example if it says this when you download it:

@echo off title Building Files "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin\javac.exe" -d ./Class/ Java/*.java Java/sign/*.java pause

and lets say you have java version 22, or w.e

you would change the last number like this,

@echo off title Building Files "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_22\bin\javac.exe" -d ./Class/ Java/*.java Java/sign/*.java pause

Edit: May Not Be Much Of A Help But I Tried…
